{
    "name": "Barometz",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any forests<br/><b>Organization</b> solitary or serving druid masters<br/><b>Treasure</b> none"
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "These massive plant juggernauts were not created by nature, but grown by druids who use them as protectors and dispensers of savage judgment. Pruned into a form resembling a stout ram, a barometz is granted a degree of intelligence by natural spirits bound into its verdant bulk.<br/><br/>Barometzes are typically found in the service of the powerful druids who cultivate them and help them protect sacred primeval forests."
        }
    ],
